name: reduce_brliib

module @jit_reduce_brliib attributes {mhlo.num_partitions = 1 : i32, mhlo.num_replicas = 1 : i32} {
  func.func public @main(%arg0: tensor<2x4xf32>) -> (tensor<f32> {jax.result_info = "result"}) {
    %cst = stablehlo.constant dense<0.000000e+00> : tensor<f32>
    %0 = stablehlo.broadcast_in_dim %cst, dims = [] : (tensor<f32>) -> tensor<2x4xf32>
    %1 = stablehlo.maximum %arg0, %0 : tensor<2x4xf32>
    %2 = stablehlo.negate %1 : tensor<2x4xf32>
    %3 = stablehlo.exponential %2 : tensor<2x4xf32>
    %cst_0 = stablehlo.constant dense<1.000000e+00> : tensor<f32>
    %4 = stablehlo.broadcast_in_dim %cst_0, dims = [] : (tensor<f32>) -> tensor<2x4xf32>
    %5 = stablehlo.add %4, %3 : tensor<2x4xf32>
    %cst_1 = stablehlo.constant dense<1.000000e+00> : tensor<f32>
    %6 = stablehlo.broadcast_in_dim %cst_1, dims = [] : (tensor<f32>) -> tensor<2x4xf32>
    %7 = stablehlo.divide %6, %5 : tensor<2x4xf32>
    %cst_2 = stablehlo.constant dense<0x7F800000> : tensor<f32>
    %8 = stablehlo.reduce(%7 init: %cst_2) applies stablehlo.minimum across dimensions = [0, 1] : (tensor<2x4xf32>, tensor<f32>) -> tensor<f32>
